		<![endif]-->

	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="header">
			<div class="header-left">
				<a href="/" class="logo">
					<img src="/images/logo-small.svg" alt="Subcultured" class="logo-image">
					<span class="logo-text">Subcultured</span>
				</a>
				<nav class="nav">
					<a href="/episodes" class="nav-item">Episodes</a>
					<a href="/blog" class="nav-item">Blog</a>
				</nav>
			</div>
			<div class="header-right">
				<a href="/subscribe" class="subscribe-button">Subscribe</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="main">
			<div class="main-content">

			</div>
			<div class="main-sidebar">
				<section>
					<h2>About</h2>
					<p>Somewhere on the Internet, a group of writers have produced hundreds of stories about a boring man and his cat. Elsewhere, a devoted Buffy the Vampire Slayer fan maintains a message board with a history of 40,000 postsâ€”all written by her.</p>

					<p>Online summer camps; dwarven kingdoms; elevator enthusiasts; the Internet is a big place. Let us be your guides through the interesting, the eccentric, and occasionally, the pornographic. Subculture is an exploration of niche Internet communities and the human behaviors that drive them.</p>

					<div class="bio">
						<div class="bio-image">
							<img src="//placehold.it/80x80" alt="Geoff Kimball">
						</div>
						<div class="bio-text">
							<p><strong>Geoff Kimball</strong> is a product designer and web developer in San Jose, California.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="bio">
						<div class="bio-image">
							<img src="//placehold.it/80x80" alt="Drew Siner">
						</div>
						<div class="bio-text">
							<p><strong>Drew Siner</strong> is a video and audio producer in Bloomington, Indiana.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Subscribe</h2>

					<a href="" class="link">iTunes</a>
					<a href="" class="link">Spotify</a>
					<a href="" class="link">Soundcloud</a>
					<a href="" class="link">RSS</a>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div id="body">
			<!--
				Flash messages allow you to display once-off status messages to users, e.g. form
				validation errors, success messages, etc
			-->
			{{#if messages}}
			<div id="flash-messages" class="container">
				{{#if messages.info}}
				<div class="alert alert-info">
						{{{flashMessages messages.info}}}
				</div>
				{{/if}}
				{{#if messages.success}}
				<div class="alert alert-success">
						{{{flashMessages messages.success}}}
				</div>
				{{/if}}
				{{#if messages.warning}}
				<div class="alert alert-warning">
						{{{flashMessages messages.warning}}}
				</div>
				{{/if}}
				{{#if messages.error}}
				<div class="alert alert-danger">
						{{{flashMessages messages.error}}}
				</div>
				{{/if}}
			</div>
			{{/if}}
			<!-- The content block should contain the body of your template's content-->
			{{{body}}}
		</div>
		<div class="container">
			<div id="footer">
				<p>Powered by <a href="http://keystonejs.com" target="_blank">KeystoneJS</a>.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
